	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A 76-year-old woman died in hospital after being mauled by a large dog in Mpumalanga on Monday morning. The elderly woman was attacked in a house in Middelburg, Mpumalanga, by the dog. ER24 paramedics arrived at the scene shortly after 9 am and found the woman in the house. According to ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring, the woman sustained several wounds that left her in a critical condition. After being stabilised by paramedics, she was taken to Middelburg's provincial hospital for urgent medical care. However, she died shortly after her arrival at the hospital. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  